        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 8:11PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 810 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking scatted heavy snow showers
moving south at 40 mph through central and Southwest MT.

HAZARD...Visibility below a half mile and ind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar and trained weather spotter indicated.

IMPACT...Poor driving visibility in heavy snow showers. Some snow
accumulations up to an inch in grassy areas.

Locations impacted include...
Portions of Central and Southwest MT.
</description>
        <instruction>Reduce driving speeds in areas of poor visibility.</instruction>
